r and bake for 45 minutes - 1 hour (140°C) until set. Turn off oven and leave meringues inside to cool completely (ideally overnight)."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Crème Pâtissière"},{"content":"Place chocolate in mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then melt <b>4 min\/37°C\/speed 2<b>. Scrape down and melt again <b>1 min\/37°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer to a bowl and keep warm. Clean mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place flour, cocoa, sugar, milk, cream, eggs and egg yolks in mixing bowl then cook <b>7 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Add vanilla and reserved melted chocolate  then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 5<b>. Pour into a bowl, cover with damp greaseproof paper and set aside to cool."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"To assemble, take a meringue circle and spread with a third of the crème pâtissière. Place another meringue circle on top and repeat, building layers to finish with a layer of crème pâtissière."},{"content":"Serve decorated with chocolate mini eggs."}],"hintsAndTricks":["The meringues and crème pâtissière can be made ahead and then assembled just before serving.","A grease-free mixing bowl and whisk are essential for well-formed meringues.","If your baking trays are very small, you may need to use three to fit all the meringue discs."],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","7h 30m","8 portions"]}